-- Banca IFIS, Telecom Italia, Zucchi May Move Today: Italian Equity Preview
-- Marco Bertacche
-- 2010-06-24T04:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/banca-ifis-telecom-italia-zucchi-may-move-today-italian-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may be
active in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  
 Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index  retreated 250.11, or 1.2
percent, to 20,358.92 in Milan.  
 Banca IFIS SpA  (IF IM): The bank will sell new shares at
3.1 euros each, according to a statement distributed through the
Italian exchange. The company said it may sell as much as 50
million euros ($61 million) of shares. The stock lost 0.3
percent to 7.38 euros.  
 Pirelli & C. SpA  (PC IM): Chairman Marco Tronchetti Provera
and Pirelli Tyre Chief Executive Officer Francesco Gori plan to
hold a press conference to present the Formula One official
supplier contract. The stock retreated 1 3.6 percent to 47.3
cents  
 Telecom Italia SpA  (TIT IM),  FastWeb SpA  (FWB IM): Italy’s
largest phone companies will meet Deputy Communications minister
Paolo Romani on a plan to develop a new-generation broadband
network in the country.  Tiscali SpA  (TIS IM), Wind
Telecomunicazioni SpA, and BT Group Plc’s local unit will take
part in the meeting. Telecom Italia retreated 0.2 percent to
96.1 cents. FastWeb was unchanged at 12.79 euros. Tiscali fell
0.5 percent, to 12.3 cents.  
 Vincenzo Zucchi SpA  (ZUC IM): Matteo Zucchi, chief
executive officer of the maker of household fabrics, told
shareholders that sales in the first five months climbed 6.4
percent, according to a statement distributed through the
Italian exchange after markets closed. The stock gained 0.3
percent to 52.2 cents.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
